# Typography: findy.place

## Brand fonts (only these two)

| Role | Font | Tailwind | Weights |
|------|------|----------|---------|
| Display / titles | **DM Serif Display** | `font-display` | 400, italic |
| UI / body / labels | **DM Sans** | `font-sans` | 300–600 |

Loaded once in `app/layout.tsx` via `next/font/google`. **Never** add Montserrat, Poppins, Inter, Geist, Arial, or other font imports.

Stacks for non-Tailwind contexts: `@/lib/typography`.

## When to use each

- **`font-display`**: h1, page titles, place names, hero headlines, auth titles, footer wordmark, loading overlay titles, italic emphasis in nav
- **`font-sans`**: body default, nav links, buttons, inputs, form labels, eyebrows (uppercase + tracking), subtitles, badges, metadata, section labels

## Rules

1. Titles and display text → `font-display`. Everything else → `font-sans` (or inherit from body).
2. Never use `font-serif`, bare `sans-serif`, or hardcoded `font-family` outside `@/lib/typography`.
3. `font-mono` only for OTP / verification codes.
4. Mascot or brand reference images may show other fonts — **ignore them**; match app fonts above.
5. Emails and Leaflet popups: import `EMAIL_FONT_DISPLAY` / `EMAIL_FONT_SANS` from `@/lib/typography`.

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Page title
<h1 className="font-display text-4xl text-fp-cream">{t("title")}</h1>

// ✅ Eyebrow label
<p className="font-sans text-[0.65rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-fp-muted">

// ❌ Wrong — generic or missing font role
<h1 className="text-4xl font-serif">
<p style={{ fontFamily: "Montserrat" }}>
```
